Class DmcFilter

  org.dmd.dmc.DmcFilter
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
ClassFilter
public abstract class DmcFilter
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

The DmcFilter provides a common base class for the implementation of code that can determine whether or not a particular Dark Matter Object meets a set of criteria. Due to the fact that there are so many different ways to specify filters or matching criteria or queries, the interface to a filter is very simplistic at this level. However, having a common filter interface means that cache implementations don't have to understand the internal workings of the filter.

public abstract java.lang.String getFilterString()
